DIGEST
SB 140 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Miller
Proposed law provides that the same proceeding may be used to open the successions of
more than one deceased person regardless of the dates of death of the deceased persons,
provided that:
(1) The deceased persons were, at the time of death, spouses or siblings; and
(2) The court has jurisdiction over each succession pursuant to Article 2811.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds C.C.P. Art. 2813)
